Employee Assistance Program (EAP)
The Company provides a confidential and voluntary assessment and referral service for family, financial, legal or other counseling. The program is available to employees and their families experiencing personal problems in the areas of marital and family relations, substance abuse, stress management, finances or legal concerns. The EAP is available 24 hours a day, seven days a week, by calling CNR Health at (800) 345-1391. In Houston there is an on-site EAP professional in the Enron Building. For an appointment with the on-site EAP professional call (713) 853-6057.
Support and Encouragement Services
The Company provides a counselor for support and encouragement regarding grief, loss and separation. The service is provided to all employees by Dr. Kelly Williams, a minister with experience on the subject of grief and coping with loss. There is no charge for up to three sessions and the services may be accessed separately from the Employee Assistance Program. For an appointment call (713) 465-4011.
